        <Label layoutX="469.0" layoutY="165.0" prefHeight="48.0" prefWidth="486.0" text="1. In a bowl sift in almond flour and icing sugar and set it aside." wrapText="true">
            <font>
                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Label layoutX="468.0" layoutY="201.0" prefHeight="87.0" prefWidth="610.0" text="2. In another clean bowl, add in aquafaba and start whipping at medium low speed. Once the aquafaba gets slightly foamy, increase the whipping speed to high and start adding caster sugar in small batches." wrapText="true">
            <font>
                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Label layoutX="470.0" layoutY="283.0" prefHeight="74.0" prefWidth="565.0" text="3. Once you reach soft peaks, add in a few drops of gel food color of your choice and continue to whip till you reach stiff peaks. This can take 7-8 minutes." wrapText="true">
            <font>
                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Label layoutX="471.0" layoutY="351.0" prefHeight="55.0" prefWidth="565.0" text="4. After reaching stiff peaks, carefully fold in the almond flour and icing sugar that was set aside before." wrapText="true">
