                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Label layoutX="473.0" layoutY="395.0" prefHeight="74.0" prefWidth="588.0" text="5. Use the cut and fold method and check the consistency of your batter after every two-three strokes of mixing." wrapText="true">
            <font>
                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Label layoutX="474.0" layoutY="459.0" prefHeight="74.0" prefWidth="565.0" text="6. Once you reach a consistency where your batter freely falls off the spatula, you can transfer the batter into a piping bag and pipe individual shells on your baking tray lined with silicone mat." wrapText="true">
            <font>
                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Label layoutX="474.0" layoutY="534.0" prefHeight="74.0" prefWidth="554.0" text="7. After piping, let shells rest for 15 minutes till they form a skin on top. Meanwhile preheat your oven at 140 degree C.Bake for 30-35 minutes." wrapText="true">
